HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1427
By Raper
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Cleveland High
School unified bowling team, 2026 TSSAA
Unified Bowling State Championship.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school athletic teams that, through their magnificent efforts,
bring honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, one such outstanding group of student athletes is the Cleveland High
School unified bowling team, which claimed the 2026 TSSAA Unified Bowling State
Championship; and
WHEREAS, in its inaugural season, the Cleveland High School unified bowling team
achieved remarkable success, culminating in a state championship victory at the highest level of
competition; and
WHEREAS, the Cleveland High School Blue Raiders completed their championship run
with victories over Gleason, Dobyns Bennett, and Station Camp in the state tournament; and
WHEREAS, a division of the Special Olympics, unified sports is committed to fostering
social inclusion through collaborative sports training and competitive experiences for individuals
with and without intellectual disabilities; and
WHEREAS, the Cleveland High School unified bowling team exemplifies this mission, as
its members have come together to compete as one team, developing lasting friendships,
confidence, and a strong sense of teamwork through their dedication and effort, and
representing inclusivity and school community at its best; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Cleveland High School unified bowling state
championship team are Elijah Bolin, Cam Garcia, and Jaxon Jones; and
HJR1427
017860
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the Cleveland High School Blue Raiders enjoy the astute leadership of
Head Coach Archie Crossland; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Cleveland High School unified bowling team have
conducted themselves in a manner appropriate to the integrity of the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, this State takes great pride in the tremendous accomplishments of those
student athletes who have excelled both in their sport and in the classroom; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the members and coach of the Cleveland High
School unified bowling team on winning the 2026 TSSAA Unified Bowling State Championship
and extend to them our best wishes for much continued success in all their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
